======================================================================
PART 1: THE UNIVERSAL TOPOLOGICAL DICTIONARY (n=5)
======================================================================

For n=5, the topology is simple: I(Ω,x) = 1 + α₁x (linear).
Every invariant is determined by a single number α₁.

  α₁    H    χ  I(1)   H+2χ   H-χ     H/χ  count
--------------------------------------------------
   0    1    1     1      3     0    1.00    120
   1    3    0     2      3     3       ∞    120
   2    5   -1     3      3     6   -5.00    240
   3  (7)   -2     4      3     9   -3.50 FORBIDDEN
   4    9   -3     5      3    12   -3.00    240
   5   11   -4     6      3    15   -2.75    120
   6   13   -5     7      3    18   -2.60    120
   7   15   -6     8      3    21   -2.50     64

★ KEY OBSERVATIONS:
  - α₁=3 is the ONLY gap → H=7 is the ONLY forbidden value at n=5
  - H + 2χ = 3 always (no correction terms)
  - H - χ = 3α₁ (exactly 3× the cycle count)
  - All 1024 tournaments accounted for: 120+120+240+240+120+120+64 = 1024

